# build/nwp-server.deny-symbols — the fail-closed AI-free guarantee (ADR-0022/0024).
#
# Each non-comment line is an extended-regex (ERE), matched case-insensitively
# against the ASSEMBLED nwp-server artifact. ANY match fails the build. This is
# the mechanical form of ADR-0022's success metric: "a `strings` check returns
# zero matches for AI-vendor library symbols."
#
# The artifact is built from an ALLOWLIST (build/nwp-server.include), so this scan
# is defence in depth: it catches an AI/CI/SaaS reference that sneaks in via an
# allowlisted file (e.g. a shared lib that grew an `import linode`).
#
# Self-hosted infra is NOT denied: the self-hosted git/artifact host, headscale,
# gotify, minisign, wireguard are all allowed. Only AI vendors, CI runners, and
# distrusted SaaS are.

# ── AI vendors / LLM clients ────────────────────────────────────────────────
anthropic
openai
\bclaude\b
\bollama\b
\bllm\b
agent-loop
\bcoder(s|-setup)?\b
claude-api

# ── CI runners / pipeline integration ───────────────────────────────────────
ci-stats
gitlab-ci
\.gitlab-ci
github/workflows

# ── Distrusted SaaS (self-hosted equivalents are preferred per CLAUDE.md) ────
linode
cloudflare
backblaze
\bb2\b
twilio
gitlab\.com
github\.com
pushover
tailscale
sigstore
cosign
